start-welcome = Welcome to the official chatbot for <a href="https://kanachyerevan.am/">Kanach Yerevan</a> activists. This bot allows you to quickly report tree damage or anomalies. Please follow our <a href="https://t.me/kanach_yerevan_news">channel</a> for updates and use our <a href="https://t.me/make_yerevan_green_again">chat</a> if you have further questions that the bot cannot answer.
map-link =
    The <a href="https://yerevan.treemaps.app/">Trees of Yerevan</a> map is our main asset. It's a "people's" map, filled by ordinary citizens, where we track the condition and health of trees. We then use this data as arguments in our communication with the city hall. To date, we have surveyed {$count} trees.
    
    You can contribute by looking after the trees around you. If you need help using the app, join our chat or come to our weekly joint mapping sessions.
report-intro =
    To help us identify the issue and the tree, please send:
    1️⃣ Close-up photos of any damage.
    2️⃣ Photos of the leaves (to identify the species).
    3️⃣ A wide shot from aside showing the tree size and nearby objects to help us locate it.

menu-start-desc = start the bot
menu-report-desc = report tree damage
menu-map-desc = view the tree map
map-button-label = Open Map
report-photo-received = Thank you! Now please send the location of where this tree is, as precise as possible.
report-location-received = Great! Now please add a short text description of what's bothering you.
report-completed =
    Thank you! We have received your report.
    
    You can still send more photos to this report, update the location by sending a new one, or use /report to start a new report.
